  • Deprecated Methods 
    Method and Description
    org.rocksdb.SstFileWriter.add(DirectSlice, DirectSlice)
    Use SstFileWriter.put(DirectSlice, DirectSlice)
    org.rocksdb.SstFileWriter.add(Slice, Slice)
    Use SstFileWriter.put(Slice, Slice)
    org.rocksdb.ColumnFamilyDescriptor.columnFamilyName()
    Use ColumnFamilyDescriptor.getName() instead.
    org.rocksdb.ColumnFamilyDescriptor.columnFamilyOptions()
    Use ColumnFamilyDescriptor.getOptions() instead.
    org.rocksdb.RocksDB.compactRange(boolean, int, int)
    Use RocksDB.compactRange(ColumnFamilyHandle, byte[], byte[], CompactRangeOptions) instead
    org.rocksdb.RocksDB.compactRange(byte[], byte[], boolean, int, int)
    Use RocksDB.compactRange(ColumnFamilyHandle, byte[], byte[], CompactRangeOptions) instead
    org.rocksdb.RocksDB.compactRange(ColumnFamilyHandle, boolean, int, int)
    Use RocksDB.compactRange(ColumnFamilyHandle, byte[], byte[], CompactRangeOptions) instead
    org.rocksdb.RocksDB.compactRange(ColumnFamilyHandle, byte[], byte[], boolean, int, int)
    Use RocksDB.compactRange(ColumnFamilyHandle, byte[], byte[], CompactRangeOptions) instead
    org.rocksdb.AbstractNativeReference.dispose()
    Instead use AbstractNativeReference.close()
    org.rocksdb.AbstractNativeReference.finalize()
    You should not rely on GC of Rocks objects, and instead should either call AbstractNativeReference.close() manually or make use of some sort of ARM (Automatic Resource Management) such as Java 7's try-with-resources statement
    org.rocksdb.DBOptionsInterface.maxBackgroundCompactions()
    Use DBOptionsInterface.setMaxBackgroundJobs(int)
    org.rocksdb.RocksDB.remove(byte[])
    Use RocksDB.delete(byte[])
    org.rocksdb.WriteBatchInterface.remove(byte[])
    Use WriteBatchInterface.delete(byte[])
    org.rocksdb.AbstractWriteBatch.remove(byte[])
    org.rocksdb.RocksDB.remove(ColumnFamilyHandle, byte[])
    Use RocksDB.delete(ColumnFamilyHandle, byte[])
    org.rocksdb.WriteBatchInterface.remove(ColumnFamilyHandle, byte[])
    Use WriteBatchInterface.delete(ColumnFamilyHandle, byte[])
    org.rocksdb.AbstractWriteBatch.remove(ColumnFamilyHandle, byte[])
    org.rocksdb.RocksDB.remove(ColumnFamilyHandle, WriteOptions, byte[])
    Use RocksDB.delete(ColumnFamilyHandle, WriteOptions, byte[])
    org.rocksdb.RocksDB.remove(WriteOptions, byte[])
    Use RocksDB.delete(WriteOptions, byte[])
    org.rocksdb.DBOptionsInterface.setBaseBackgroundCompactions(int)
    Use DBOptionsInterface.setMaxBackgroundJobs(int)
    org.rocksdb.DBOptionsInterface.setMaxBackgroundFlushes(int)
    Use DBOptionsInterface.setMaxBackgroundJobs(int)
  • Deprecated Constructors 
    Constructor and Description
    org.rocksdb.SstFileWriter(EnvOptions, Options, AbstractComparator>)
    Use SstFileWriter.SstFileWriter(EnvOptions, Options). Passing an explicit comparator is deprecated in lieu of passing the comparator as part of options. Use the other constructor instead.
